  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="head">
        <div class="eyebrow on-dark"><span class="num" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5)">No. 05</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>Common questions</div>
        <h2 style="margin-top: 14px;">What members ask before they join.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="list">
        <details open>
          <summary>
            <span class="num">Q · 01</span>
            <span class="q">We already have vendor relationships we&rsquo;re happy with. Do we have to switch?</span>
            <svg class="chev" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="a">No. Co-op membership doesn&rsquo;t require replacing existing vendors. Members typically start by directing new or supplemental spend through preferred partners and evaluate the savings before changing anything else. The question isn&rsquo;t whether your current vendors are good &mdash; it&rsquo;s whether your pricing terms are as strong as they could be.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            <span class="num">Q · 02</span>
            <span class="q">We&rsquo;re too small for this to make a meaningful difference.</span>
            <svg class="chev" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="a">The model works precisely because small and mid-size companies pool volume together. A company too small to negotiate meaningful terms on its own is exactly the profile Innovia was designed for. The benefits compound across vendor categories &mdash; and every one of them points back at the communities you serve.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            <span class="num">Q · 03</span>
            <span class="q">How does Innovia make money? Is there a catch?</span>
            <svg class="chev" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="a placeholder placeholder-inline" style="display: block;">[Client to confirm: membership fee structure and revenue model so we can answer this with confidence and specificity. This is a priority intake question.]</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            <span class="num">Q · 04</span>
            <span class="q">How is this different from a referral program or kickback arrangement?</span>
            <svg class="chev" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="a">Innovia operates as a member-owned cooperative. Members hold a stake in the organization, and the co-op exists to serve them &mdash; not to monetize them on the back end. <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Client to confirm: exact governance and patronage details]</span></div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            <span class="num">Q · 05</span>
            <span class="q">We don&rsquo;t have time to manage another program.</span>
            <svg class="chev" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="a">Innovia is designed to reduce work, not add it. Vendor terms are pre-negotiated, peer-group meetings are scheduled quarterly with calendars sent a year in advance, and the portal is opt-in. Once onboarded, the operational lift is minimal.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>
            <span class="num">Q · 06</span>
            <span class="q">Does joining mean giving up our brand or independence?</span>
            <svg class="chev" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="a">No. The cooperative deliberately exists outside the acquisition path. You keep your name, your contracts, your team, and your board relationships. The co-op layers leverage and intelligence on top of an independent firm &mdash; it doesn&rsquo;t replace one.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

